Both deliverables are written. Summary of findings:

**Headline result.** feature_027 is the only treatment with heterogeneous PFS effects in this cohort. It increases PFS by +4.98 months (95% CI 4.97-4.99) only in the subgroup defined by **feature_006=0 AND feature_023=0 AND feature_022=0 AND feature_005<5** (n=9,326, 18.7% of cohort). Outside that subgroup, treatment effect is null (-0.003 mo, p=0.24). All four predicates are necessary — relaxing any one dilutes the effect substantially.

**Prognostic structure.** Independent prognostic factors (R²=0.993 final model): feature_015 (continuous, +0.176/unit, KPS-like), feature_001 (ordinal, -1.17/level, stage-like), feature_014 (binary, -1.37), feature_019 (+0.485), feature_025 (-0.078), log(feature_021) (-0.097).

**Key insight:** feature_006/023/022/005 are *purely predictive* (treatment-effect modifiers), not prognostic — their apparent main effects vanish once the eligibility×treatment interaction is in the model. The mutual exclusivity of feature_023/011/022 suggests a categorical biomarker classification (RAS/BRAF-like in CRC).

